@NODE History "Programming History of PowerCrawler"
@TOC "Main"

@{B}V 1.31@{UB}		o Layer control requester to switch transparency/visibility
		  of any layer off and on.

		o PortuguĻse catalog by @{" ATO " LINK "ATO.readme/main"}

		o Since V39 (OS 3.0) and V40 (OS 3.1) amigaguide datatype
		  use different layout/size for links (buttons) this guide
		  looked crappy on V40. I have fixed up the guide a little
		  bit and now it's acceptable on V40. Unfortunately on V39
		  the guide will probably now look even worse than the old
		  guide did on V40 :(

		o No more limitations and nerve requesters in unregistered
		  version. Shareware fee was reduced dramatically, because
		  only one person (in three years!) was kind enough to re-
		  gister :( Maybe I asked too much but you can't tell me
		  this anymore - I think the new fee is more than fair ...


@{B}V 1.20@{UB}		o Users who want to register now only need a Keyfile that
		  removes the restrictions and the Nerve Requester.

		o New Mask-Blit-Routine. Should make the rendering of
		  Multi-Layer Maps work correctly on GFX-Boards. The
		  Tooltypes @{" MASKBMF " LINK "TTMASKBMF"} and @{" PREZOOMMASKBMF " LINK "TTPREZOOMMASKBMF"} probably have
		  to be changed, too, when using GFX-Board Screenmodes.


@{B}V 1.10+@{UB}		o Added my EMail address to documentation


@{B}V 1.10@{UB}		o Removed a bug that could cause a Crash or Dead-Lock
		  when aborting the Map-Settings

		o Changed look of some GUI-Objects (like Pop-Up Menus)

		o Removed some minor bugs

		o Added Online-Help

		o Gadgets are now highlighted when pressing a Shortcut

		o New logo (raytraced with MaxonCinema 4D V1.5, 256 cols)

		o Added some more Shortcuts

		o Popup Menus on Edit-Screen can now also be accessed by
		  Keyboard

		o Completely redone Catalog Files (now V 2.0). The ones
		  from PowerCrawler 1.00 can't be used anymore.

		o New Function: Flipping actual Block/Brush

		o Improved Information Window

		o PowerCrawler can now be forced to use the Built In
		  Language (TOOLTYPE "NOLOCALE")

		o PowerCrawler can now be forced to load a Catalog even
		  for the Built In Language (TOOLTYPE "FORCELOCALE")

		o Tooltypes can now be changed from inside the program

		o Edit-Screen has now a lot more Menus

		o Map Window can now be changed between Backdrop-Mode and
		  Normal-Mode

		o Toolbox can now be closed

		o When using the Scrollers in the Map-Window for Page-
		  Scrolling not one Page was scrolled but one Page minus
		  one Block. (No real bug, but I think it's better so!)

		o If internal PIC-Loader or IFF-Library returns 'This is not
		  an Iff-File' you can now choose between aborting or trying
		  to load the picture using the Datatypes-Loader.

		o PowerCrawler can now be iconified when holding down SHIFT
		  while pressing the CLOSE-GADGET, the QUIT-GADGET or ESC.

		o New Tooltypes "ICONIFYX", "ICONIFYY", "NICESTRING"

		o The coordinates of the Scrollers in the Map-Window were
		  not calculated correctly.

		o Powercrawler can now use external Picture-Loaders (see
		  Developer-Files)

		o It's now possible to pop up the Brush-PopUp-Menu under
		  the Mouse Pointer

		o The Reflexion-Table Editor had (and still seems to have)
		  some bugs.

		o If a Window would be too large when using the selected
		  Font, Topaz.font 8 will be used automatically. (Well, not
		  all windows do this, yet!)


@{B}V 1.00@{UB}		o First release

		o Unregistered Version only
@ENDNODE
@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
@TOC "Main"

PowerCrawler is a new Map-Editor with some @{" Features " LINK "Features"} never seen before.
It is OS-Conform and should (I don't know) also work on GFX-Boards. Is is
very easy to use and supports Localization, external Loaders/Savers, Data-
types and the Iff.Library.

PowerCrawler is @{" Shareware " LINK "LegalStuff"}. Read how to @{" register " LINK "Registering"} now!!!

@{U}Requirements:@{UU}	AMIGA OS 3.0
		CPU 68000
		1 MByte RAM


@{U}Installation:@{UU}	Double-click the Install Icon or copy the PowerCrawler-
		Drawer whereever you want. PowerCrawler needs the Assign
		"PowerCrawler:" which should point to the PowerCrawler-
		Drawer. The Installation-Script adds the Assign to the
		User-Startup. You can also use the ClickMe-Icon to create
		the Assign.

@{U}Developing:@{UU}	PowerCrawler was written in Pascal using Highspeed-Pascal
		V1.20 from HiSoft on this machine:

		@{B}COMPUTER	:@{UB} AMIGA 1200
		@{B}CPU		:@{UB} 68030-50 Mhz
		@{B}FPU		:@{UB} 68882-50 Mhz
		@{B}RAM		:@{UB} 2 MB CHIP + 16 MB FAST
		@{B}HARDDISK	:@{UB} IDE-2,5" WESTERN DIGITAL 540 MB
		@{B}CD-ROM		:@{UB} HITACHI CDR 7930 8x SPEED


		@{U}That's the only machine PowerCrawler has been tested on!@{UU}
@ENDNODE

