@NODE EditCloseGadget "Edit-Screen: Leaving Edit-Mode"
@TOC "ManualEditingMaps"

By activating the Close-Gadget in the Map-Window you leave Edit-Mode. This
is necessary if you want to save the Map/Project, change some Settings or
something like that.
@ENDNODE

@NODE EditMapWindow "Edit-Screen: Map-Window"
@TOC "ManualEditingMaps"

In this window you can edit your Map. The Map can be scrolled with the
Scrollers or the Cursor-Keys: <SHIFT> + CurorKey scrolls 1 Page
                              <ALT>   + CursorKey scrolls to the Start/End

See @{" Shortcuts " LINK "EditShortCuts"}!
@ENDNODE

@NODE EditShortCuts "Edit-Screen: Shortcuts/Control"
@TOC "ManualEditingMaps"

<F1>		Activates @{" Block-Mode " LINK "EditToolBlock"}.
<F2>		Activates @{" Brush-Mode " LINK "EditToolBrush"}.

<F6>		Activates @{" Replace-Mode " LINK "EditToolReplace"}.
<F7>            Activates @{" Matte-Mode   " LINK "EditToolMatte"}.

<F3>		Activates the Zoom PopUp-Menu.
<F4>		Activates the Brush PopUp-Menu.
<F5>		Activates the Special Operations PopUp-Menu.

<F9>		Resets the Windows' Position/Size to Preset #1.
<F10>           Resets the Windows' Position/Size to Preset #2.

@{B}<DEL>@{UB}		Sets the actual Block to the <Transparent Block> (0 or -1).
		This is useful if you have Block -1 as transparent Block
		because you can't reach it in the Blocks-Screen.

<TAB>		Cycles through MapWindow/ToolWindow/BrushWindow. This is
		limited if @{" Autopoint " LINK "MSAutoPoint"} is on.

<CURSOR-KEYS>	Allow you to scroll through the Map (you can also use it
		with <SHIFT> (Page-Scrolling), <ALT> (Init/End-Scrolling)).

@{B}<SPACE>@{UB}		Brings to front the @{" Blocks-Screen " LINK "BlocksScreen"}!

@{B}<RMB>@{UB}		The Right Mouse-Button brings to front the @{" Blocks-Screen" LINK "BlocksScreen"}!

<CTRL>+<LMB>	Use this to drag (scroll) the map.

<MMB>		If your mouse has three buttons you can use the middle one
		to drag the map.

<CTRL>+<RMB>	Pops up the Brush-Menu right under the Mouse-Pointer

<D>		Activates @{" Freehand-Drawing  " LINK "EditToolFree"}.
<V>		Activates @{" Line-Drawing      " LINK "EditToolLine"}.
<R>		Activates @{" Rectangle-Drawing " LINK "EditToolRect"}.
<SHIFT> + <R>	Activates @{" Filled R.-Drawing " LINK "EditToolRectF"}.
<A>		Activates @{" Airbrush-Drawing  " LINK "EditToolAirB"}.
<F>		Activates @{" Filling-Tool      " LINK "EditToolFill"}.
<B>		Activates @{" Brush-Cutting     " LINK "EditToolCut"}.
<SHIFT> + <K>	Activates @{" Clear-Window      " LINK "EditToolClear"}.

<RETURN>	Selects the whole map. Works with: Rectangle
						   Filled Rectangle
						   Brush-Cutting

<U>		@{" Undo " LINK "EditToolUndo"}

<1>,<2> .. <0>	Sets the Actual Layer (1..10).

<+>		Zoom + @{" Rel. Zoomfactor " LINK "TTRelZoom"}
<->		Zoom - @{" Rel. Zoomfactor " LINK "TTRelZoom"}

<ALT-RIGHT> +	Zoom + @{" Rel. Zoomfactor " LINK "TTRelZoom"}
<LMB>

<ALT-RIGHT>   + Zoom - @{" Rel. Zoomfactor " LINK "TTRelZoom"}
<SHIFT-RIGHT> +
<LMB>

</>		Scrolls through the Brushes (-)
<*>		Scrolls through the Brushes (+)

<[>		Scrolls through the Blocks (-)
<]>		Scrolls through the Blocks (+)
@ENDNODE
