|oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|@{BG SHINE}||oO|||oO@{BG FILL}|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO||
»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»@{BG SHINE}»»»»»»»»»@{BG FILL}»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»
 :    :    :    :    :    :    :    :    @{BG SHINE}:    :   @{BG FILL} :    :    :    :    :   
/»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»@{BG SHINE}»\\ /»»\\ @{BG FILL}/»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ /»»\\ 
|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»@{BG SHINE}|T|»»|T@{BG FILL}|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T|»»|T
|oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|@{BG SHINE}||oO||@{BG FILL}|oO|||oO|||oO|||oO|||oO||
»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»@{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG FILL}»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»
@{BG BACKGROUND}
  @{I}As you see the Group of Blocks is used like a Pattern.
  If you're using a single Block or 1x1-Brush you'll get a normal line.@{UI}


@{B}o One Point/Column:@{UB}

  Only one point per Column will be drawn. The Column's Width is the hori-
  zontal number of Blocks of your Group of Blocks/Brush or 1 if you are
  using a single Block.
  
@{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}


     @{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
     @{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
     @{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
     @{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
     @{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}


          @{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
          @{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
          @{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
          @{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
          @{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}


               @{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
               @{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
               @{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
               @{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
               @{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}
  

@{B}o One Point/Row:@{UB}

  Only one point per Row will be drawn. The Row's Height is the vertical
  number of Blocks of your Group of Blocks/Brush or 1 if you are
  using a simple Block.
  
@{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
@{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}
	     @{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
	     @{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
	     @{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
	     @{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
	     @{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}
		          @{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
		          @{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
		          @{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
		          @{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
		          @{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}
			               @{BG SHINE} :   @{BG BACKGROUND}
			   	       @{BG SHINE}/»»\\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
			               @{BG SHINE}|»»|T@{BG BACKGROUND}
			               @{BG SHINE}|oO||@{BG BACKGROUND}
			               @{BG SHINE}»»»»»@{BG BACKGROUND}
  

@{B}Hint:@{UB}

One Point/Column(Row) is very useful if you have a Group of Blocks/Brush
that is used to draw an uneven Path/Area/Hill/...

@{B}Example:@{UB}


@{I}You have a 5 x 3 Brush which looks like this:@{UI}

	@{BG SHINE}|»\\  @{BG BACKGROUND}
	@{BG SHINE}|  \\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
	@{BG SHINE}|___\\
@{BG BACKGROUND}

@{I}You want to get this:@{UI}

	@{BG SHINE}|»\\  @{BG BACKGROUND}
	@{BG SHINE}|  \\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
	@{BG SHINE}|___\\
@{BG BACKGROUND}	 * @{BG SHINE}|»\\  @{BG BACKGROUND}
	   @{BG SHINE}|  \\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
	   @{BG SHINE}|___\\
@{BG BACKGROUND}	      @{BG SHINE}|»\\  @{BG BACKGROUND}
	      @{BG SHINE}|  \\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
	      @{BG SHINE}|___\\
@{BG BACKGROUND}	         @{BG SHINE}|»\\  @{BG BACKGROUND}
	         @{BG SHINE}|  \\ @{BG BACKGROUND}
	         @{BG SHINE}|___\\
@{BG BACKGROUND}

@{I}Simply do this:@{UI}

1) Set Line-Mode to @{B}One Point/Row@{UB}.
2) Select Start-Position of Line.
3) Move Marker to the second Position the Brush has to be drawn at(*).
4) Hold down LEFT ALT-KEY (if Offset (StartPosition - SecondBrushPosition)
   X is greater than Offset Y) or RIGHT ALT-KEY (if Offset (StartPositon -
   SecondBrushPosition) Y is greater than Offset X) to lock the Angle.
5) Release the Mouse-Button at Line-End-Position.
6) That's it!
@ENDNODE

@NODE AirSettings "Edit-Screen: Airbrush-Settings"
@PREV "LineSettings"
@NEXT "FillSettings"
@TOC "EditToolWindow"

Click twice the Airbrush-Gadget to bring up the Settings-Window.
It looks like this:

	@{BG FILL}@{"ū" LINK "EditToolWindow"}@{"Airbrush                  " LINK "AirSettings"}@{BG BACKGROUND}
	|           Type           |
	| @{"         <Type>         " LINK "AirSettings"} |
	+--------------------------+
	|  Size   @{"8    " LINK "AirSettings"}     @{"8    " LINK "AirSettings"} |
	+---------------+----------+
	|     Pause     | Movement |
	| @{"         " LINK "AirSettings"}@{"<" LINK "AirSettings"}@{">" LINK "AirSettings"} |    @{"ū" LINK "AirSettings"}     |
	+---------------+----------+


o Type:     This Cycle-Gadget defines the Type of Airbrush. It can be
	    RECTANGLE or CIRCLE.
        
o Size:     Defines the Size of the Airbrush (in Blocks). If <Type> is
 	    CIRCLE then Size is the diameter.
        
o Pause:    This Scroll-Gadget sets the delay between two Airbrush-Drawings.
            Move it left for fast Airbrushing and right for slow action.
        
o Movement: If checked the next AirBrush-Point will only be drawn after
            having moved the Mouse.

@ENDNODE

@NODE FillSettings "Edit-Screen: Fill-Settings"
@PREV "AirSettings"
@NEXT "EditToolWindow"
@TOC "EditToolWindow"

Click twice the Fill-Gadget to bring up the Settings-Window.
It looks like this:

	@{BG FILL}@{"ū" LINK "EditToolWindow"}@{"Fill                      " LINK "FillSettings"}@{BG BACKGROUND}
	|           Type           |
	| @{"         <Type>         " LINK "FillSettings"} |
	+--------------------------+
	| @{" Set Reference Point... " LINK "FillSettings"} |
	+--------------------------+

o Type : This Cycle-Gadget defines the Fill-Mode:

	- NORMAL fills all connected Blocks of the actual Layer that have
	  the same number the Block in the actual Layer where you have
	  clicked with the Mouse has.
	  
	- VERTICAL fills a vertical Line scanning the actual Layer using
	  the number of the Block in the actual Layer where you have
	  clicked with the Mouse.
	  
	- HORIZONTAL fills a horizontal Line scanning the actual Layer
	  using the number of the Block in the actual Layer where you have
	  clicked with the Mouse.
	  
	@{I}An Example might explain it better:@{UI}


	You fill with Block @{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND} at Position @{BG FILL}0@{BG BACKGROUND}:

	-> Before Filling the Map looks like this:	

	456623464664664460
	064455004000046460
	465200000000000466
        456000000000000896
        566660000@{BG FILL}0@{BG BACKGROUND}00046542
        456000000046655555
        455500000000046523
        565556000000008652
        660006894646612338

	- @{B}NORMAL FILLING@{UB}

	456623464664664460
	064455@{BG SHINE}**@{BG BACKGROUND}4@{BG SHINE}****@{BG BACKGROUND}46460
	4652@{BG SHINE}***********@{BG BACKGROUND}466
        456@{BG SHINE}************@{BG BACKGROUND}896
        56666@{BG SHINE}********@{BG BACKGROUND}46542
        456@{BG SHINE}*******@{BG BACKGROUND}46655555
        4555@{BG SHINE}*********@{BG BACKGROUND}46523
        565556@{BG SHINE}********@{BG BACKGROUND}8652
        660006894646612338

	- @{B}VERTICAL FILLING@{UB}

	456623464664664460
	064455004@{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND}00046460
	465200000@{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND}00000466
        456000000@{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND}00000896
        566660000@{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND}00046542
        456000000@{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND}46655555
        455500000@{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND}00046523
        565556000@{BG SHINE}*@{BG BACKGROUND}00008652
        660006894646612338

	- @{B}HORIZONTAL FILLING@{UB}

	456623464664664460
	064455004000046460
	465200000000000466
        456000000000000896
        56666@{BG SHINE}********@{BG BACKGROUND}46542
        456000000046655555
        455500000000046523
        565556000000008652
        660006894646612338


o Reference Point :

  Lets you select a Reference Point useful when Filling with a Group of
  Blocks/Brush to make sure that at a certain Position the Group of Blocks
  /Brush is drawn as it is (and not scrolled because of the Pattern-
  Filling).



@{B}Note:@{UB} The Fill-Routine only checks the actual Layer to find out where to
      fill and where not. For example in Matte-Mode Area-Scanning is done
      in the actual Layer but Filling in one of the next Layers.

      Vertical/Horizontal Filling does not need any @{" FILLBUFFERS " LINK "TTFillBuffers"}!
@ENDNODE

@NODE EditSpecialWindow "Edit-Screen: SpecialWindow"
@TOC "ManualEditingMaps"

The Special-Window looks like this:

@{BG FILL}@{" " LINK "EditSpecialWindow"}@{BG BACKGROUND}»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»»|
@{BG FILL}@{" " LINK "EditSpecialWindow"}@{BG BACKGROUND} @{"ū" Link "ESShowCoords"} @{"            " LINK "ESCoords"} @{"?" LINK "ESZoom"} @{" 100% " LINK "ESZoomPopUp"} @{"  My Brush  " LINK "ESBrushPopUP"} @{" Special-Operations " LINK "ESEditMenu"} |
@{BG FILL}@{" " LINK "EditSpecialWindow"}@{BG BACKGROUND}______________________________________________________________|

@ENDNODE

